I'm tired of syncing config files.

http://necoro.wordpress.com/2009/10/08/managing-your-configuration-files-with-git-and-stgit/
http://necoro.wordpress.com/2009/10/10/managing-your-configuration-files-with-git-revisited/
http://www.silassewell.com/blog/2009/03/08/profile-management-with-git-and-github/

To get on a new server:

 1. ssh with forwarding to the server
 1. git clone git@github.com:ryepup/dotfiles.git
 1. cd dotfiles
 1. git checkout server
 1. cd
 1. mv dotfiles/.git .config.git
 1. shopt -s dotglob
 1. mv -i dotfiles/* .